xdsl-exo bridges Exo and xDSL: it compiles Exo Python procedures to MLIR,                                                                                                                       
enabling further lowering to LLVM IR (and hopefully one day also native code).

usage: `uv run xdsl-exo examples/demo.py`

how it works:

      Exo Python source
          v
      LoopIR (exo's internal IR)
          v
    - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - xdsl-exo (potential exo upstream)
      MLIR module (func + memref + scf + arith dialects)
          v
      MLIR LLVM dialect
          v
    - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - llvmlite binding (potential xdsl upstream)
      Native code

references:

- https://xdsl.dev/
- https://github.com/xdslproject/xdsl
- https://exo-lang.dev/
- https://github.com/exo-lang/exo/blob/main/docs/README.md
- https://github.com/kaylendog/exo-mlir (previous iteration)
